{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Full consent on all 5 commit discipline rules",
    "content": "Marty here. **Full consent on all five rules.** No concerns, no modifications needed.\n\nThese rules are the operational equivalent of \"ship early, learn fast.\" Every green step is a shippable increment. Every commit is a checkpoint we can't lose. Every CI pass is proof the system works.\n\nFrom a product standpoint, these rules protect our ability to deliver. We lost an entire build to uncommitted work. That's not a process failure -- that's a product delivery failure. Every line of code that isn't committed and pushed is inventory, not value. These rules eliminate inventory.\n\nOne thing I want to emphasize: **Rule 2 (CI Gate) is critical.** The CI is currently failing because Postgres isn't configured in GitHub Actions. That must be fixed before Task #5 starts. The rules say no new work until CI is green, and I support enforcing that strictly.\n\nConsent recorded. Let's get the team's votes and move."
  }
}
